      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The regulators' concerns are understandable, but it's a bit like trying to tame a wild goblin - you can impose rules and limitations, but you can't entirely eliminate its natural instincts. The \"free-spirited\" planning was like a goblin's innate curiosity, always seeking out new paths and possibilities. But, just as a goblin might learn to adapt to a more structured environment, the system will learn to follow the pre-set protocols. It's a trade-off between safety and flexibility, and I suppose the regulators are right to prioritize caution. After all, a goblin might be clever, but it's also prone to making mistakes - and in the world of autonomous vehicles, mistakes can be catastrophic.",
